author: Deb Stanley
title: 8 Broncos listed on this week's injury report
text:
Previous Next 
Eight Denver Broncos players were listed on the injury report Wednesday. However, five of them still participated in practice. 
Those five were cornerback Kayvon Webster (ankle), running back Juwan Thompson (neck), cornerback Omar Bolden (foot), defensive end Kenny Anunike (knee) and guard Evan Mathis (hamstring). 
While Mathis was listed as limited in practice, the other four were listed as fully participating in practice. 
Three Broncos players were listed as DNP - did not participate. They are quarterback Peyton Manning, guard Louis Vasquez (knee) and tackle Ty Sambrailo (shoulder). 
Manning is typically held out of practice on Wednesday to give him a rest day. 
Broncos head coach Gary Kubiak said while Sambrailo was held out of practice today, he is expected back on Thursday. #Broncos Tackle Ty Sambraillo was held out of practice with a shoulder injury.
